  "prompt": "Why is Pepto-Bismol so effective against diarrhea?",
  "response": "Pepto-Bismol (bismuth subsalicylate) is effective against diarrhea for several reasons:\n\n1. Anti-inflammatory properties: It reduces inflammation in the digestive tract, which can help alleviate diarrhea symptoms.\n\n2. Antimicrobial action: The active ingredient has mild antibacterial effects against some organisms that cause diarrhea, such as E. coli.\n\n3. Coating effect: It forms a protective coating on the intestinal lining, which helps reduce irritation and fluid secretion.\n\n4. Reduces intestinal fluid and electrolyte loss: It helps decrease the amount of fluid in the intestines, which can help firm up stools.\n\n5. Prostaglandin inhibition: Similar to aspirin, it can reduce prostaglandin production, which plays a role in intestinal inflammation.\n\nThese combined actions make Pepto-Bismol an effective over-the-counter treatment for mild cases of diarrhea, providing relief from symptoms and helping to speed up recovery.",
